    "description": "Okura Industrial Co., Ltd. manufactures and sells polyethylene and polypropylene products in Japan. It operates through three segments: Synthetic Resin Business, New Material Business, and Construction Materials Business. It offers plastic packaging film for food and other packaging to industrial materials; and Lamitop Masker HR, a masking film used for two-tone color automotive roof. The company also provides thermoplastic polyurethane elastomer film under the Silklon brand name; and solventless acrylic adhesive, including anaerobic adhesives, UV curable adhesive, and two-component curing adhesive under the Yumen Brand name. In addition, it offers optical functional films, particle board, engineered wood boards, plywood, and other engineered wood products; and engages in lumber processing and housing site development business, as well as sells housing. The company's products are used in electronic information, automotive, and medicine and welfare industries. Okura Industrial Co., Ltd. was formerly known as Shikoku Industry Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Okura Industrial Co., Ltd. in November 1955. Okura Industrial Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 1947 and is headquartered in Marugame, Japan."
